      "correspondence_text": "Var(N_mol) ~ rho^0.66 (CI [0.61,0.70]) EXCLUDES the proper-area target rho^0.5; Var/A_proper drifts (CV=0.66). The MEAN already failed (F-031: <N_mol> ~ rho^0.54 area but S_full ~ rho^1) and now the FLUCTUATION also fails to give a clean area-law -> the 4D dS area-law is ABSENT on BOTH the mean and the variance axes. A second independent negative strengthening F-031. The molecule count is super-Poisson with a growing Fano (~rho^0.12): the variance exponent 0.66 sits ABOVE the area 0.5 but BELOW the volumetric 1.0, i.e. clustering of near-null straddling links on the codim-2 surface lifts Var above area scaling without reaching a volume law. Unlike F-035 (Fano=1, Poisson), the count is NOT Poisson here, so the variance carries no clean area signal."
